{
  "texts": [
    "We further code relevant tweets for stance and diagnostic, prognostic, and motivational framing strategies (Table 2).",
    "Stance can take one of three mutually-exclusive values: progressive (pro-gun control, pro-immigration, pro-LGBTQ), conservative (pro-gun rights, anti-immigration, anti-LGBTQ), or neutral/unclear from the text.",
    "Guided by Benford and Snow (2000) and Goh and Pang (2016), we operationalize and code for diagnostic framing based on the presence of any of two sub-categories: problem identification and blame attribution.",
    "Similarly, we code for prognostic framing based on the presence of any of four sub-categories based in Benford and Snow (2000) 's definition:",
    "proposing solutions, discussing movement tactics, expressing solidarity, and engaging in counterframing."
  ]
}